Beijing’s market supervision department carries out comprehensive law enforcement before the holiday, and commodity prices are basically stable
China News Service, Beijing, September 27 (Reporter Du Yan) In order to strengthen market supervision and law enforcement before the holiday, the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision inspected more than 2,000 business entities of various types on the eve of the National Day.
The inspection showed that the supply of daily necessities such as grains, oils, meat, fruits, vegetables, eggs, and milk sold in the market was sufficient, commodity prices were basically stable, no serious violations of laws and regulations were found, and the market operation order was generally stable.
Today, reporters learned from the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Regulation that the bureau has launched a &quot;Comprehensive Law Enforcement Inspection Day&quot; activity across the city, focusing on all elements and all aspects of law enforcement in key areas and areas such as price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and drugs, and commerce. Inspect and comprehensively regulate market operation order.
According to reports, the five law enforcement teams of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision, including price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and drug, and commerce, have coordinated and closely cooperated. The teams are led by the heads of each law enforcement agency and are divided into groups to conduct joint law enforcement on some randomly selected business entities. examine.
During the inspection, law enforcement officers focused on price behavior, advertising, food safety, measurement standards, production safety systems and other contents.
The market supervision bureaus of each district also simultaneously organized joint law enforcement inspections, dispatching more than 1,600 law enforcement personnel and inspecting more than 2,000 business entities of various types. The inspection results showed that daily necessities such as grains, oils, meat, fruits, vegetables, eggs, and milk sold in the market The supply is sufficient, commodity prices are basically stable, operators can operate in compliance with the law, no serious violations of laws and regulations have been found, and the market operation order is generally stable.
The Beijing Municipal Administration for Market Regulation stated that it will strengthen emergency duties during the National Day, continue to conduct inspections and patrols on the market, and quickly handle various market supervision issues in accordance with the law. Once verified, illegal business activities reported by the public will be dealt with seriously in accordance with the law to effectively protect consumers. legitimate rights and interests.
