The United Nations International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) released a report on the 26th stating that Iran has begun using advanced centrifuges to accelerate the production of enriched uranium, further violating the 2015 nuclear agreement with world powers.
According to comprehensive foreign media reports, the IAEA report stated that advanced centrifuges at Iran&#39;s Natanz Nuclear Facility &quot;are accumulating or are preparing to accumulate enriched uranium.&quot;
Since U.S. President Trump withdrew from the nuclear deal and imposed sanctions on Iran in May last year, Iran has been gradually violating the restrictions of the 2015 nuclear agreement with major powers.
The agreement stipulates that Iran can only use first-generation IR-1 centrifuges to refine uranium.
The deal&#39;s other signatories, Britain, China, France, Germany and Russia, have been trying to save it, but Tehran has repeatedly accused Europe of not doing enough.
