The Republic is about to celebrate its 70th anniversary. The spotlights of various media suddenly turn on, making many images that we don&#39;t usually remember shine brightly - it is they who have brought every trace of those shining days to us. Bring heat energy, bring light source...
However, if a hero walks beside you, he may seem ordinary, just like you or me.
Yuan Longping devoted himself to rice research and bred improved seeds for cultivation all over the world, which made more than one billion people no longer in danger of hunger. He has done a great job. He is also like an old farmer who likes to walk in the fields; Nan Ren Dong, the chief scientist who worked hard to make China&#39;s &quot;eyes of heaven&quot; open. He is a person, a whole life, a pot, and only does one thing in his life. He is eating cold steamed buns in the mountains of Guizhou, and he is no different from the old man in the village; Zhou Ruchang, Hongxue Jia, a village boy who was enlightened very late, still looks like a child even when he is old, has learned both Chinese and Western knowledge, has a head of disheveled white hair, talks about knowledge knowingly, and likes to burst into laughter; Qin Yi, who is famous in the movie &quot;Half the Sky&quot; The artist, who is over ninety years old, still travels on the plateau for six or seven hours a day for rehearsals, and is still willing to play an unknown old maid in &quot;The Legend of the Demon Cat&quot;...
They seek benevolence and get benevolence, and live a simple, simple and persistent life. As long as they are immersed in a career that outsiders don&#39;t understand but they cherish, they will easily become happy, without caring about fame, wealth and glory.
Just like in Jin Yong&#39;s novel, the sweeping monk in the Sutra Pavilion of Shaolin Temple, although he has amazing martial arts skills, he is neither ostentatious nor shy, neither happy nor sad.
Behind every &quot;sweeping monk&quot; and every innocent heart, there is a responsibility for the family and country other than myself.
The responsibility for the country lies not only on the shoulders of heroes, but also in the hands of hundreds of millions of people.
Once, the words of a female middle school student were widely circulated by netizens, &quot;When a hero passes by, someone always sits on the roadside and applauds... I don&#39;t want to be a hero, I want to be the person who sits on the roadside and applauds. &quot;
In fact, being a hero and applauding heroes are not contradictory.
People applauding on the roadside are also passing on heat and light, and are themselves luminaries.
Ordinary people like you and me, there are always some opportunities in life, there are some moments, there is a kind of accumulation over time that also shapes the appearance of a hero.
Zou Bihua, an outstanding judge in Shanghai, shoulders the important task of judicial reform, but at the annual meeting, he asked the master of the communication room to tell his story. He sent and received countless newspaper letters in a year without making any mistakes. &quot;Doing simple things well is not simple.&quot; , Zou Bihua led the judges to give applause to this old &quot;sweeping monk&quot;-style transceiver.
This is the sympathy between heroes, it is one hero applauding another hero.
The sweeping monk has the Shaolin Temple Sutra Pavilion, Yuan Longping has the vast rice experimental field, Nan Rendong has the &quot;eye of the sky&quot;, Qin Yi has the stage, Zhou Ruchang has the forum... Whether you can be a hero depends not only on your own efforts, but also on good qualities. environment and positive incentives.
For example, the &quot;Chinese Sky Eye&quot; seems to be a myth now.
In the 1990s, China&#39;s scientific and technological circles were still struggling to climb the ladder, and the novelist Liu Cixin had not yet started writing &quot;The Three-Body Problem&quot;.
The most powerful &quot;eye&quot; at that time was Arecibo, a single-aperture radio telescope in the valley of the island of Puerto Rico in the United States. With a diameter of 350 meters, it was considered to be the &quot;unsurpassable&quot; largest in the world.
At that time, the diameter of the Chinese radio telescope was less than one-tenth of that of others.
However, Nan Rendong, who enjoyed world-class scientific research conditions and salary in Japan, insisted on returning to China and brought back an almost crazy idea: to build a new generation of radio &quot;large telescope&quot; in China to receive more messages from outer space!
China is full of waste and is waiting for prosperity. Why invest huge sums of money just to play for the stars?
The motherland trusted Nan Rendong, and the &quot;Sky Eye&quot; project was launched with great success.
It took 12 years to select the site, and another 9 years from project establishment to completion.
With the opening of the 500-meter-diameter &quot;Eye in the Sky&quot;, China has completed a large-scale scientific project that has no precedent and is &quot;unique in the world.&quot;
Therefore, the &quot;Eye of the Sky&quot; is amazing, Nan Rendong and others are amazing, and the Republic of China, which is tolerant and has a high vision, is amazing.
With the trust of the country and the goodwill of the people, Nan Rendong and others have the opportunity to become the soul of the country and the courage of the people.
There are young talents and white-haired heroes walking by kindly, and people applauding gently on the roadside. This kind of country is very beautiful and harmonious.
Garbage classification education enters Jilin kindergarten for the first time. Environmental protection concept starts from childhood
On the 27th, a kindergarten in Jilin City, Jilin Province conducted a garbage classification education class to teach children to distinguish recyclable garbage from other types of garbage.
It is reported that this is the first time that garbage classification has been introduced into local early childhood education classes.
A few days ago, nine departments in Jilin Province jointly issued the &quot;Jilin Province Work Plan for Promoting the Classification and Treatment of Domestic Waste in Prefecture-Level Municipalities.&quot;
In 2019, based on Changchun City’s pilot program of mandatory domestic waste classification, the province decided to carry out domestic waste classification work in prefecture-level cities.
Jilin City is one of them.
We hope that through this event, we can achieve the effect of using children to drive families and kindergartens to drive society, and advocate the concept of environmental protection.
Liu Lijuan, executive director of Hifaner International Kindergarten, which hosted the event, said.
On the same day, the principal read out an environmental protection initiative, hoping that garbage classification would start from children.
After the children performed the &quot;Low Carbon Beibei&quot; dance, they divided into groups to play a garbage sorting game.
The instructor also distributed &quot;recyclable&quot; and &quot;other garbage&quot; labels and suggested that the children stick the labels to the trash cans and record a short video when they go home.
Liu Lijuan introduced that the kindergarten has always advocated the concept of low carbon and green environmental protection and regularly holds environmental lectures.
There are also sortable trash cans at the garbage disposal areas in the park, with the categories marked on them.
The teacher teaches the children what recyclable garbage is. Photo by Cang Yan
According to preliminary statistics, Jilin Province produced approximately 5.4652 million tons of urban domestic waste in 2018, all of which entered domestic waste treatment plants for processing.
Among them, 3.2929 million tons were sanitary landfill, 2.0923 million tons were incinerated, and 80.1 thousand tons were processed through comprehensive utilization technology.
After years of hard work, all cities and counties in the province have the ability to harmlessly process domestic waste.
The &quot;Jilin Province Work Plan for Promoting the Classification and Treatment of Municipal Domestic Waste at the Prefecture Level&quot; that has been issued clearly requires the in-depth implementation of activities such as introducing garbage classification into campuses, teaching materials, and classrooms, through the creation of garbage classification songs, ballads, comics, micro videos, etc. The works strengthen the interaction between students and parents and achieve the effect of &quot;educating a child, influencing a family, driving a community, and cultivating a new generation.&quot;
