Chirac&#39;s political legacy will last forever after his death
On the 26th local time, former French President Chirac passed away suddenly at the age of 86.
At a time when the world is undergoing profound changes unseen in a century, the many political legacies left behind by this French politician when he was in power still deserve our praise.
Chirac served as French president for 12 years in a charismatic manner.
He not only inherited the independent diplomatic spirit of de Gaulleism, but also firmly supported European integration. He was a representative figure in pursuing the &quot;European Dream.&quot;
At the same time, he also strongly advocates world multipolarity and multilateralism, and is a politician with strategic vision.
Because of this, the French media evaluated him as &quot;an outstanding representative of France on the world stage.&quot;
One of Chirac&#39;s most talked-about political decisions was his opposition to the US-led war in Iraq.
Under his leadership, France joined hands with Germany to withstand American pressure and was at the forefront of the anti-war movement.
One year after the war broke out, he predicted that the war in Iraq would lead to an intensification of terrorist activities and make the world more dangerous.
