Pro-establishment members of the Hong Kong SAR Legislative Council signed a petition to oppose the US bill related to Hong Kong
Some pro-establishment members of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region issued a joint statement on the 27th, expressing strong opposition to the passage of the &quot;Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act of 2019&quot; by the Foreign Affairs Committee of the House and Senate of the United States Congress.
The statement, signed by 40 pro-establishment lawmakers, stated that the rights currently enjoyed by Hong Kong are conferred by the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, including maintaining the status of a free trade port and a separate customs territory, in the economy, finance, shipping, trade, communications, tourism, and culture. , sports and other fields, in the name of &quot;Hong Kong, China&quot;, it trades, cooperates and develops relations with different countries and regions around the world, and signs and implements bilateral and multilateral agreements.
These rights are not conferred by any foreign government or legislative body.
Hong Kong has always strictly abided by international agreements, international rules, laws and business ethics, conducted business with different countries and regions, and participated in cooperation in many related fields, with remarkable achievements that are obvious to all.
The statement said that the US Senate and House of Representatives Foreign Affairs Committee&#39;s move to pass the relevant bill was unnecessary and was only in response to the call of its agents to cause trouble in Hong Kong, as a means of grossly intervening in Hong Kong&#39;s internal affairs and gaining political chips for its agents in Hong Kong.
Establishment lawmakers deeply regret the move by the US Congress and strongly oppose it.
The statement pointed out that Hong Kong is an important trading partner and the largest source of trade surplus for the United States.
Hong Kong&#39;s excellent rule of law, fair and free business environment, and clean society make it a good choice for American businessmen to do business.
If the U.S. Congress passes this bill, it will not only hit the interests of Hong Kong and the United States itself, but also make Sino-U.S. relations worse. It will not benefit anything and will harm others and itself.
The statement stated that Hong Kong will, as always, unswervingly implement the &quot;one country, two systems&quot; policy, continue to enjoy the rights granted by the Basic Law, and earnestly perform its obligations.
No matter in the past, present or future, Hong Kong will continue to make due contributions to the international community and international trade.
According to a report by &quot;European Times&quot; on the 26th, the two houses of the French Parliament will discuss immigration policy reform next week.
French President Macron recently stated that France cannot &quot;accept everyone&quot;, but at the same time it must strive to &quot;accommodate properly&quot;.
According to reports, Macron is trying to find a compromise line on immigration matters to slow down the impact of the upcoming debate.
Recently, in an interview during the general debate of the United Nations General Assembly in New York, Macron expressed his hope for a true &quot;two-pronged&quot; plan on immigration policy to find a balance between humanitarianism and efficiency.
Macron said: &quot;If France wants to be able to accept (immigrants) properly, it cannot accept everyone.&quot;
Macron listed four priorities for immigration policy: grant asylum status to refugees in need of protection as soon as possible; promote the integration of immigrants more efficiently; receive and protect all immigrants entering French territory; and resettle those who have entered France illegally and are not suitable to stay more efficiently. people.
Whether illegal immigrants should be protected by the National Medical Assistance (AME) system has been the most discussed topic in the past.
Macron said he hoped to &quot;evaluate&quot; the system but not abolish it, but impose certain restrictions on it.
After Macron made these remarks, Le Pen, the leader of the far-right &quot;National Alliance&quot;, tweeted that Macron&#39;s statement was &quot;empty talk.&quot;
Senate President Raschel, a member of the right-wing Republican Party, also said that immigration policy should be discussed in a &quot;moderate&quot; but &quot;face to reality&quot; manner, indirectly criticizing Macron.
Varao, a member of the left-wing Socialist Party, believes that France should &quot;accept more and better&quot; when it comes to immigration and criticized Macron for &quot;manipulating&quot; this issue.
The report pointed out that the new version of the &quot;Asylum and Immigration Law&quot; has been enacted for a year. It has caused disagreements within the ruling party, but at the same time it has been unable to appease the right-wing opposition parties.
In the next general election in 2022, the topic of immigration policy will once again become the focus of the far-right attack. Macron needs to make a difference on this issue, but at the same time he will risk angering left-wingers within the ruling party.
According to reports, the French National Assembly’s lower house will debate immigration policy from September 30, and the Senate will debate it from October 2.
There are signs that China&#39;s A-shares are ushering in a &quot;buyback wave&quot;, with many listed companies spending &quot;real money&quot; to buy back company shares.
According to statistics from financial data service provider Orient Fortune, as of the 27th, the total amount of repurchases implemented by A-share listed companies in 2019 has exceeded 100 billion yuan (RMB, the same below), far exceeding the data for the same period in previous years, setting a record for A-share stock repurchase funds A record high in volume.
In this regard, Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Maikerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said that the overall valuation of the A-share market this year is low, and repurchasing shares at a relatively low price will help listed companies improve the efficiency of the use of funds, and also reflects The willingness of listed companies to proactively manage market value and their abundant cash flow will help boost investor confidence.
In addition, the continuously improving share repurchase system has also promoted listed companies to actively carry out share repurchases.
For example, at the beginning of this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange issued detailed implementation rules for listed companies to repurchase shares, providing listed companies with detailed specifications and guidelines for share repurchases.
According to media statistics, since this year, listed companies that have implemented shareholding increase and repurchase plans are mainly concentrated in the infrastructure industry, real estate industry, information technology industry, and electronic equipment manufacturing industry.
In addition, judging from the amount of repurchase payments, 6 listed companies have repurchase amounts of more than 1 billion yuan this year.
Among them, Yili shares top the list, with a repurchase amount of more than 5 billion yuan.
What impact will stock buybacks by listed companies have on the market?
Zhao Xijun, deputy dean of the School of Finance at Renmin University of China, said in an interview with a reporter from China News Service that buybacks on the one hand show that listed companies have strong economic strength and good financial status, and have the ability to maintain stock price stability, giving investors confidence. On the other hand, it also shows that listed companies and their controlling shareholders are responsible for the company, the market and investors.
The former is based on the company&#39;s good operating performance, while the latter requires listed companies and their controlling shareholders to have higher quality.
For the capital market, these are the core basic elements.
The repurchase of shares by listed companies will help boost investor confidence and support the stock prices of listed companies.
According to Orient Securities research reports, based on the estimated number of stock repurchases set by A-share listed companies since the beginning of this year and the average transaction price of repurchased stocks, the incremental funds that repurchases will bring to the A-share market this year It is expected to exceed 150 billion yuan.
It took nearly two months to restore the large-scale mural &quot;Tianhou&#39;s Holy Relics&quot; in Tianjin&#39;s Tianhou Palace, a key cultural heritage site, on the 26th. It will be reopened to the public during the National Day this year.
&quot;The Holy Relics of the Queen of Heaven&quot; is a large-scale traditional mural that comprehensively reflects Mazu&#39;s life.
Approved by relevant state departments, it was drawn by Cai Changkui, the former director of Tianjin Folklore Museum (Tianhou Temple) from 1991 to 1994.
It is understood that this mural was painted on the south and north walls of the main hall of Thean Hou Palace. It is 32 meters long and 2.6 meters high. It is divided into upper and lower parts. It tells more than 30 stories such as the birth of the Queen, crossing the sea on a seat, and her ascension to heaven. 358 The individual characters reproduce Mazu’s life story.
Cai Changkui said that in recent years, Tianjin has been rainy in summer and dry in winter. This &quot;wet and dry&quot; situation has caused the murals to crack, and the cracked parts account for 60% of the entire mural area.
In order to protect and save the murals of Mazu&#39;s deeds, the Nankai District Ancient Culture Street Management Committee and Tianhou Palace in Tianjin launched a restoration project of the main hall of Tianhou Palace and the murals in the palace.
The restoration project was led by Cai Changkui, and four famous Chinese painters were invited to participate.
The restoration work was based on the principle of &quot;repairing the old as before&quot;. At the same time, some adjustments were made to the original murals, and the imperfect parts of the murals were supplemented and repaired.
During the restoration, we also made innovations and attempts in colors, materials, pen and ink, etc.
After restoration, the style, spirituality, spirit and artistic style of the original murals were maintained.
Tianhou Palace was built in 1326, formerly known as Tianfei Palace, commonly known as the Empress’ Palace. It has been renovated many times and is the oldest building complex in Tianjin. It is also one of the earliest existing Mazu temples in China.
On September 25, the commissioning ceremony of Beijing Daxing International Airport was held grandly.
The shape of the terminal building of Beijing Daxing International Airport means &quot;Phoenix spreading its wings&quot; and is known as the first of the &quot;Seven Wonders of the New World&quot;.
Currently, Beijing Capital International Airport is operating at overload. Last year it carried more than 100 million passengers, becoming the second airport in the world with an annual passenger throughput of over 100 million after Atlanta Airport in the United States.
It is expected that by 2022, the passenger throughput of Beijing Daxing International Airport will reach 45 million, with international flights accounting for 20%; by 2025, the passenger throughput will reach 72 million, with international flights accounting for 30%.
As a &quot;new national gate&quot;, how cool is it?
Beijing Daxing International Airport is located between Daxing District in Beijing and Guangyang District in Langfang City, Hebei Province. The straight-line distance from Tiananmen Square is 46 kilometers. It is currently the largest new airport in the world.
The terminal&#39;s roof steel structure has a ground projected area of 180,000 square meters, which is the size of 25 standard football fields.
Beijing Daxing International Airport is the world&#39;s first terminal with two arrival floors and two departure floors - F1-F4 are international arrivals, domestic arrivals, domestic departures and international departures respectively.
The double-decker bridge connecting the expressway and the airport outside the terminal corresponds to terminals F3 and F4 respectively - the upper level for international departures, and both floors for domestic departures.
The maiden flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport opened the era of &quot;dual airports&quot; in Beijing.
The new airport is positioned as a large international aviation hub, a new source of power for national development, and a comprehensive transportation hub in the Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei region that supports the construction of Xiongan New Area. As of now, a total of 66 airlines are interested in settling in Beijing Daxing International Airport, 20 of which are within the territory. Airlines, 46 Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan and foreign airlines, and the flight schedules of each airline have been approved one after another.
In the winter and spring flight season of 2019, Beijing Daxing International Airport is expected to open 116 routes, including 101 domestic routes and 15 international routes; covering 112 destinations around the world, including 97 domestic destinations and 15 international destinations.
This forms a &quot;dual-hub&quot; airport pattern with coordinated development, moderate competition, and world-class competitiveness with Beijing Capital International Airport. It not only relieves the operating pressure of Capital Airport&#39;s saturated capacity, but also better meets the rapid growth of air transportation in Beijing and surrounding areas. meet the urgent needs and effectively enhance the international competitiveness of my country&#39;s civil aviation industry.
In order to ensure efficiency and quality, Beijing Daxing International Airport fully considers the geographical location, the relationship between the airport and surrounding airspace and the operating environment. The airport runway adopts an &quot;omnidirectional&quot; layout for the first time in China, adopts the world&#39;s largest air traffic control automation system, and establishes China&#39;s largest terminal control area can maximize aviation operation efficiency.
For the first time, an airport of this size in China has used a domestic automatic baggage processing and information management system, adopting an innovative baggage transmission mode to improve the baggage system processing efficiency.
The maiden flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport heralds the phoenix spreading its wings and taking off in a cool way.
This new airport, which has created more than 40 international and domestic firsts and has a localization rate of more than 98%, will definitely have a direct and indirect economic impact on the industries in surrounding areas and inject airport vitality into Beijing&#39;s economic development.
