Wang Boxiang, former Secretary of the Shouguang County Party Committee in Shandong Province - a pure heart to strengthen the county and enrich the people - Xinhuanet
Wang Boxiang was born in Shouguang, Shandong Province in February 1943. He started working in 1967 and has successively served as secretary of the township party committee, secretary of the county party committee, and mayor.
In 1986, Wang Boxiang was appointed secretary of the Shouguang County Party Committee in Shandong Province. At that time, Shouguang was a poor county in Weifang.
During the five years he served in Shouguang, Wang Boxiang had a heart for the people and concentrated on doing three things: first, promoting the industrialization of vegetables; second, developing the Shoubei salt-alkali flats; third, laying the foundation for industrial turnaround, allowing Shouguang people to Puff your pockets and straighten your back.
Shouguang farmers have a tradition of growing vegetables, and they also have experience in growing vegetables.
In the early 1980s, farmers in Shouguang had a good harvest of vegetables, but they could not sell them and were rotting in the fields.
Wang Boxiang’s research found that the key to grasping vegetables is to improve circulation.
Shouguang took the lead in building a vegetable wholesale market, kicking off the development of a market economy.
Party members and cadres must take the lead. If something goes wrong, the county will bear all the losses.
In 1989, with the support of Wang Boxiang, 17 party members including Wang Leyi of Sanyuanzhu Village built 17 winter-heated vegetable greenhouses. That year, 17 &quot;double-thousand-yuan households&quot; emerged in the village.
Subsequently, a promotion team was set up in the county. Mobilized by Wang Boxiang, Wang Leyi toured various towns and villages to provide guidance; more than 5,000 vegetable greenhouses were promoted in the first year, and then vegetable greenhouses were spread throughout the county and even the country like a prairie fire.
For thousands of years, the 1.6 million acres of land in Shoubei have been composed of salt-alkali shoals and shallow tidal flats.
The life of the local people is very difficult.
Shounan has a vegetable greenhouse, what should Shoubei do?
Wang Boxiang organized hundreds of thousands of people to hold a big battle and camped on the deserted alkali beach for forty or fifty days.
Wang Boxiang and the leading cadres in the county had food and accommodation on the construction site. Like migrant workers, they pushed carts and carried burdens, and slept in the open air. When the people saw them, they gave them thumbs up and admired them from the bottom of their hearts... At that time, Shoubei developed a shrimp pond of 150,000 acres. , 200,000 acres of salt fields, 600,000 acres of cotton fields, and a &quot;treasure basin&quot; developed on the saline-alkali tidal flats.
In July 1986, Wang Boxiang attended the Weifang Industrial Conference for the first time as secretary of the county party committee.
During the meeting, a &quot;Comparison Table of Industrial Economic Figures of Twelve Counties and Urban Areas in Weifang City&quot; was issued. At first glance, Shouguang&#39;s total industrial output value is not bad, ranking fourth.
But if the raw salt is removed, Shouguang&#39;s pure industrial output value is only 119 million yuan, ranking third from the bottom.
Wang Boxiang took a group of more than 70 people to study abroad and went to other places to &quot;change their minds.&quot;
Less than a year after returning, the county invested 150 million yuan and launched 77 projects.
Since then, &quot;Learning Groups&quot; have been organized every year to travel to Shenzhen, Dongguan, Shanghai and other places to learn from the teachings.
Shouguang lacks enterprises and even more entrepreneurs.
Wang Boxiang presided over a special meeting to make the final decision: a public selection of factory directors and managers throughout the county, and 40 &quot;enterprising and capable people&quot; stood out and were promoted to the front line of industry.
In 1991, Shouguang entered the ranks of the top 100 counties in the country, and Wang Boxiang was transferred to the deputy mayor of Weifang City.
What he left behind are more than 200,000 vegetable greenhouses, 1.2 million acres of cotton fields, salt fields, and shrimp ponds, 4,854 enterprises, more than 100,000 &quot;ten thousand-yuan households&quot;, and a cadre team recognized by the people. The people of Shouguang still affectionately call him &quot;our Secretary Boxiang&quot;.
On September 26, local time, State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi chaired the Foreign Ministers’ Meeting of China and African Members of the Security Council at the United Nations Headquarters in New York.
Current African Security Council members Cote d&#39;Ivoire&#39;s Foreign Minister Tano, Equatorial Guinea&#39;s Foreign Minister Oyono, South Africa&#39;s Foreign Minister Pandor, and incoming members Niger&#39;s Foreign Minister Kara and Tunisia&#39;s Foreign Minister Jessinaoui attended the meeting.
Wang Yi put forward four suggestions on strengthening cooperation between China and Africa in the Security Council.
First, strength comes from unity.
The biggest challenge in the current international situation is unilateralism. The direct consequence is that the basic norms of international relations are challenged, the role of the United Nations is affected, and the interests of developing countries and small and medium-sized countries, including African countries, are harmed.
To cope with this challenge, China and Africa need to work hand in hand and shoulder to shoulder. Only through unity can we have strength.
In the Security Council, the three African countries speak with one voice, and the focus is not just on the three votes, but on the entire African continent.
When China and Africa stand together, it will not just be 4 votes, but will lead other countries to follow suit and influence and shape the agenda of the Security Council.
Since 2018, China has established a &quot;3+1&quot; coordination mechanism with African members of the Security Council, and we must make full use of this coordination mechanism.
Second, resolve disputes through consultation.
China has always advocated political settlement of hot-spot issues. Africa has a good tradition of consultation and has experience in successful mediation by African regional and sub-regional organizations.
Many complex problems on the Security Council&#39;s agenda, especially hotspots in Africa, are mostly caused by colonialism, and some are directly related to external factors.
We must jointly make good use of Chapter 6 of the United Nations Charter and give full play to the role of the United Nations in mediation and mediation.
Third, rely on independence to seek self-improvement.
African countries and people understand Africa&#39;s problems best, and Africa also has the ability and wisdom to solve its own problems.
When dealing with hot-spot issues in Africa, the Security Council should listen to and respect Africa&#39;s wishes, play the role of regional and sub-regional organizations, and encourage and support endogenous solutions from Africa.
China is willing to strengthen coordination with Africa and firmly promote capacity building for independent peace operations in Africa.
Fourth, rely on development to treat the root causes.
China and African countries are both developing countries. We must insist on putting economic and social development first and support each other&#39;s development paths chosen by each other.
China is willing to closely integrate the joint construction of the &quot;Belt and Road&quot; with the African Union&#39;s Agenda 2063, the United Nations 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development, and the development strategies of African countries, so as to help African countries enhance their development capabilities and eliminate the root causes of conflicts.
We must jointly promote the United Nations to increase investment in African development.
The Ebola epidemic broke out again in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. China has and will continue to provide all-out assistance, providing manpower and material assistance within its capacity. China is also willing to coordinate actions with African countries, mobilize the United Nations, WHO and others to increase assistance and give full play to the United Nations The role of Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
The neonatology department and others worked together to save the little life.
thrilling!
The pregnant mother of her second child had an early seizure. On the way to the hospital in a hurry, a 32-week premature baby was eagerly born in the passenger seat of her father&#39;s car.
Fortunately, the obstetrician and neonatologist responded promptly and saved this little life.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th, and 21st, the Obstetrics and Neonatology Department of Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days, and the other two were born in the 120 ambulance. All were premature babies at 29 weeks.
Ms. Cheng is a pregnant mother with her second child. At 7 a.m. on September 19, she felt a little pain in her stomach. Thinking that she was already 32 weeks pregnant and her first child was also premature, she packed up her belongings and prepared to go directly to the hospital after taking a shower. .
After 9:30, Ms. Cheng packed up and asked her husband to drive from his home in Xudong to the hospital.
Unexpectedly, not long after the car drove out of the house, the baby could not wait to be born in the passenger seat of his father&#39;s car.
20 minutes later, Ms. Cheng and her baby finally arrived at the Obstetrics and Gynecology Building of Hubei Maternal and Child Health Hospital.
When the hospital security saw the panicked couple and baby, they immediately notified the obstetrics and delivery room. Four doctors including deputy chief physician Zhang Huan and midwife Liu Yanyan rushed downstairs with the delivery bag and umbilical cord tray.
&quot;At that time, the mother was half-lying on the passenger side of the car, with amniotic fluid and blood underneath her body. A baby boy was next to her, still connected to the umbilical cord. &quot;
Zhang Huan inquired and learned that the baby was a 32-week premature infant. The parents did not have time to wrap the baby during the journey. The early autumn morning was already chilly. His skin was pale from the cold, he did not cry, and his limbs were limp.
Liu Yanyan hurried to the passenger seat to treat the baby&#39;s umbilical cord. Zhang Huan got in from the cab, quickly opened the delivery bag, used the treatment towel inside and the delivery bag wrapping cloth to wrap the baby in several layers to keep warm, and cleared the newborn&#39;s respiratory tract. (As shown in the picture), and then carried the baby to the neonatal department on the 12th floor.
After the neonatology department doctors learned the news, they immediately rushed to the nurse station to rescue the premature baby on the spot.
At that time, the baby&#39;s face turned purple and he was suffocating and hypoxic. The doctor immediately performed a tracheal intubation on him. In less than a minute, the baby&#39;s heartbeat resumed and his skin color gradually returned to rosy. The resuscitation was successful.
After being admitted to the hospital, the 32-week-old baby was put on an invasive ventilator. After continuous rescue, his breathing became stable and he was successfully weaned off the ventilator the next day.
After a week of treatment, the baby&#39;s vital signs are now stable, his breathing is smooth, and he has started to feed a small amount of milk.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th, and 21st, the obstetrics and neonatology departments of the hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days. The other two were born in the 120 ambulance, both 29. Zhou&#39;s premature baby is currently being actively treated in the neonatal department.
Sun Guoqiang, director of the obstetrics department of the Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital, said that in recent years, the Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital has received many babies born on the subway or in private cars. If this situation is not handled well, it may threaten the life safety of the mother and child.
Director Sun reminded that pregnant mothers should come to the hospital immediately if they experience abdominal pain, water rupture, redness, etc.
In case of giving birth at home or on the road, the mother should try to lie on her back as much as possible. She can put a blanket under her buttocks to prevent the baby&#39;s head from hitting the ground after delivery. The baby should be kept warm immediately after delivery and sent to the nearest hospital as soon as possible.
