China releases &quot;China and the United Nations&quot; and reports on climate change, sustainable development and other issues - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, United Nations, September 26 (Reporter Xu Xiaolei and Wang Wen) On September 26, the Chinese delegation attending the 74th United Nations General Assembly officially released &quot;China and the United Nations - China&#39;s Position Paper at the 74th United Nations General Assembly&quot; and &quot;United Nations Climate Change Action Summit: China&#39;s Position and Actions&quot;, &quot;China&#39;s Progress Report on Implementing the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development (2019)&quot;, &quot;Big Earth Data Supporting the Sustainable Development Goals Report&quot; and other 4 documents.
&quot;China and the United Nations - China&#39;s Position Paper at the 74th Session of the United Nations General Assembly&quot; summarizes the achievements and development of China&#39;s cooperation with the United Nations in various fields since the founding of the People&#39;s Republic of China 70 years ago, especially since the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China.
It was pointed out that Chinese President Xi Jinping’s proposal to promote the building of a community with a shared future for mankind has become the banner of major-country diplomacy with Chinese characteristics.
Under the guidance of Xi Jinping Thought on Diplomacy, China has participated in international affairs in a more active and proactive manner, made greater contributions to world peace and development, and assumed more responsibilities.
China has always been a builder of world peace, a contributor to global development and a defender of the international order.
The document introduces China&#39;s important contributions to the three pillars of peace, development and human rights of the United Nations from ten aspects.
Reaffirmed that China firmly supports and practices multilateralism and supports the United Nations in playing a central role in international affairs; pointed out that China&#39;s development and the development of the world resonate at the same frequency and the two promote each other; emphasized that in the face of major changes in the world unseen in a century, a continuous A developing China will contribute more and more positive energy to the world.
&quot;United Nations Climate Action Summit: China&#39;s Position and Actions&quot; closely follows the nine major action areas of the United Nations Climate Action Summit and introduces China&#39;s policy propositions on international cooperation in addressing climate change and China&#39;s achievements in addressing climate change.
As the largest developing country in the world, China regards addressing climate change as an intrinsic requirement for its own sustainable development and its responsibility to build a community with a shared future for mankind. It will continue to overcome many difficulties and challenges facing its own development, firmly safeguard multilateralism, and implement international Commitment to fully promote the comprehensive and effective implementation of the Paris Agreement.
&quot;China&#39;s Progress Report on the Implementation of the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development (2019)&quot; is the second progress report released by China after the implementation progress report released in 2017.
The report comprehensively summarizes China&#39;s measures, progress, challenges and next steps in implementing the 2030 Agenda, demonstrating China&#39;s determination and achievements in implementing new development concepts and achieving high-quality development.
The cases included in the report such as targeted poverty alleviation, innovation-led development, ecological civilization construction, rural revitalization, and joint construction of the “Belt and Road” will provide useful reference for other countries to implement the 2030 Agenda.
The &quot;Report on Big Earth Data Supporting the Sustainable Development Goals&quot; demonstrates China&#39;s exploration and practice of using Big Earth Data technology to support the implementation of the 2030 Agenda and policy decision-making, and reveals the application value and prospects of relevant technologies and methods for monitoring and evaluating the Sustainable Development Goals. , providing a new perspective and new support for the international community to fill the gaps in data and methodology and accelerate the implementation of the 2030 Agenda.
