The main shaft of my country&#39;s deepest railway shaft has been dug to the end.
Xinhua News Agency, Kunming, September 27 (Reporter Ding Yiquan) According to my country Railway Tunnel Bureau Group Co., Ltd., the main shaft of the No. 1 shaft of the Gaoligongshan Tunnel of the Dali-Ruili Railway, the longest railway tunnel in China, was successfully excavated on the 27th. In the end, the depth of the shaft was 762.59 meters, breaking the record for the deepest railway shaft in China.
In tunnel construction, shafts can improve tunnel ventilation, improve ballast removal efficiency, and ensure construction safety.
Song Tao, chief engineer of the shaft work area of the Darui Project Department of China Railway Tunnel Bureau, said: &quot;After the main shaft of No. 1 shaft of the Gaoligongshan Tunnel is successfully excavated to the end, it will help promote the construction of the construction shaft bottom parking lot and open up more space for the later construction of main holes and horizontal guides. A working face will speed up the construction progress of the entire Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel. &quot;
Song Tao introduced that the construction of the No. 1 shaft of the Gaoligongshan Tunnel adopted the well-drilling method and was equipped with a well-drilling derrick, a well-drilling stabilizer, a well-drilling winch, an integral mobile metal formwork, an FJD-6A umbrella drill, a central rotary rock grabber and other large-scale Professional machinery has formed a &quot;four-in-one&quot; mechanized assembly line including mechanized excavation system, ballast removal system, suspension system, winch lifting system, etc., realizing the full mechanization of drilling, blasting, ballast removal, formwork installation, concrete pouring, etc. operation, greatly speeding up the construction progress.
It is understood that the Dali-Ruili Railway runs from Dali in the east to Ruili in the west, with a total length of approximately 331 kilometers and a design speed of 140 kilometers per hour. It is an important part of the China-Myanmar international railway channel.
The Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel is 34.538 kilometers long and is the longest railway tunnel in my country.
