Qingyang, Gansu: Hu sheep carry &quot;Poverty Alleviation Scripture&quot;.
Autumn in September brings color to the Loess Plateau.
In the Yimin Breeding Professional Cooperative in Yima Town, 58-year-old villager Xia Weili filled the trough in the sheepfold with the last spade of fodder and stood by the trough, watching the white Hu sheep chewing each bite.
&quot;It&#39;s so delicious. When it&#39;s full of fat in autumn and winter, it can be sold at a good price. &quot;
Xia Weili said that he feeds the sheep &quot;special nutritious meals&quot; every day, cleans, sterilizes and disinfects them regularly, and takes care of them carefully without neglecting them.
Xia Weili has been raising sheep for more than 20 years. It was not until he came to work in the cooperative that he realized how extensive sheep farming was in the past.
Xia Weili is from Xia Laochi Village, Yima Town, Qingcheng County, Qingyang City, Gansu Province.
His neighbors are all sheep farmers, but they adhere to the traditional free-range way of raising sheep, resulting in poor quality sheep and a small number of sheep.
In June this year, under the guidance of the government, 140 poor households in the village joined the cooperative, and everything began to change.
Xia Weili immersed himself in breeding all day long because he always had a strong energy in his heart.
The people who bought shares were all from poor households. They all entrusted their sheep to the cooperative, and they all depended on him whether they would get dividends and sell them at a higher price at the end of the year.
Fortunately, with the guidance of technical personnel, he gradually learned to prevent epidemics, mastered scientific feeding, and became one of the few &quot;good masters&quot; in breeding in the village.
Yimin Breeding Professional Cooperative is a standardized cooperative with a total of 16 sheep sheds and nearly 1,400 Hu sheep.
Zou Tao, the person in charge of the cooperative, said that the standardized sheep sheds are very professional both inside and outside.
&quot;The wool is thick and dense, and it is easy to breed bacteria. Hu sheep cannot stay in hot and humid places. The sheep shed must be built in a place surrounded by ditches on three sides, and a fan must be installed for ventilation and heat dissipation. &quot;
Zou Tao said that in order to prevent the epidemic, the sheep sheds need to be regularly sprayed and disinfected, and the sheep should be vaccinated three to four times in the first quarter.
In addition to living well, the &quot;little sheep&quot; also have to eat a mixture of corn silage, wheat straw, alfalfa, etc., and have a wide enough &quot;playground&quot; to stretch their muscles.
The cooperative adopts the method of trusteeship and breeding to guide local farmers to put fine-bred Hu sheep here, and uniformly raise, manage and sell them to achieve fine-bred, scientific, standardized and intensive breeding.
Today, 140 poor households with sheep as shares receive dividends of more than 6,000 yuan per household every year, and 4 registered poverty alleviation targets are working in the cooperative.
From &quot;grazing in the mountains&quot; to &quot;precision feeding&quot;, from &quot;local mating&quot; to &quot;artificial insemination&quot;, from &quot;looking at the body shape and feeling the belly&quot; to &quot;doing B-ultrasounds one by one&quot;... In Qingyang, Gansu, mutton sheep breeding is not only It is a change in the way of feeding. The &quot;leading enterprise + cooperative + farmer&quot; model has changed the scene of &quot;raising sheep on the hillside and selling sheep in the market&quot;, overcoming the weakness of traditional agriculture and animal husbandry, and the poor life of farmers. Because modern sheep farming has become better.
Zou Tao said that if the market price is weak, Gansu Zhongsheng Agriculture and Animal Husbandry Development Co., Ltd., a leading local company, will purchase the product at a market protection price of 27 yuan per kilogram to help farmers diversify market risks.
Xu Jianfeng, general consultant of Gansu Zhongsheng Agriculture and Animal Husbandry Development Co., Ltd., said that the company has driven more and more poor households to recite the &quot;Sheep Sutra&quot; by providing loan guarantees, breeding sheep supply, order breeding, quotation acquisition, unified processing and sales and other services to poor households. .
In Qingyang, at least 8,200 poor families have achieved a stable increase in income by &quot;joining&quot; Zhongsheng Agriculture and Animal Husbandry&#39;s forage breeding, improved seed breeding, large-scale breeding, slaughtering and segmentation, and market sales.
Qingyang City is located in the northern agro-pastoral transition zone and is rich in forage resources.
At present, there are 913 large-scale mutton sheep farms and cooperatives in the city, with more than 5 million mutton sheep raised, and two processing production lines with a slaughter capacity of 1.3 million mutton sheep have been built. The sheep are becoming the &quot;leader&quot; in the local industrial poverty alleviation. .
French Finance Minister says tax cuts will exceed 10 billion euros next year and calls on Germany to follow suit
PARIS, Sept 26 (Reuters) - France will cut taxes by more than 10 billion euros ($10.9 billion) next year, and Germany should keep up with France&#39;s fiscal stimulus to restore economic growth, Finance Minister Bruno Le Maire said on Thursday. boost the sluggish economy.
When introducing France&#39;s 2020 budget, Le Maire said that the European Central Bank&#39;s latest monetary easing measures created an opportunity for member governments that can afford it to increase investment.
The European Central Bank cut interest rates to a record low on September 12 and plans to restart bond purchases to lower borrowing costs, hoping to stimulate economic recovery and push up inflation.
&quot;Low interest rates will not bring prosperity back to Europe. Monetary policy measures are necessary but not sufficient,&quot; Le Maire told reporters.
&quot;Germany needs to invest, and it needs to invest now, the sooner the better. Don&#39;t wait until the situation gets worse,&quot; he added.
He has made this appeal to Germany many times.
France has implemented tax cuts of more than 10 billion euros this year, which has greatly boosted France&#39;s economic growth.
The global economy has lost momentum, and the German economy, which relies on exports, has borne the brunt.
Le Maire pointed out that the tax burden on French families will be reduced by 9.3 billion euros next year, including 5 billion euros in income tax cuts.
In addition, with the gradual implementation of the reduction of the corporate tax rate from 33.3% to 25% over a five-year period, corporate tax burdens will be reduced by nearly 1 billion euros.
