Pilot the notification and commitment system in areas such as low-risk food production licenses, and delegate the management powers of foreign enterprise representative offices to free trade zones
On the 27th, the Shanghai Municipal Administration for Market Regulation and the Pudong New Area Government signed a working memorandum to launch 20 market supervision reform measures, some of which are the first to be piloted in the country.
According to reports, notification commitment means that the administrative agency notifies the applicant in writing of the conditions and requirements stipulated in laws and regulations at one time when handling relevant licensing registration matters.
After the applicant signs the commitment, the administrative agency can handle it directly.
According to the memorandum, the Shanghai market supervision department will support the Pudong New Area and the Shanghai Pilot Free Trade Zone in piloting the notification and commitment system in three areas, including company name registration, simple process and low-risk food production licenses, and type approval of some measuring instruments, so that companies can accurately It is more convenient to enter.
Shanghai Shao Wansheng Food Co., Ltd. obtained the &quot;Food Production License&quot; on the spot through notification and commitment on the 27th, becoming the first company to enjoy the pilot bonus.
The person in charge of the company said that food licenses can also be obtained on the spot, and a &quot;deficiency-tolerant acceptance&quot; method is adopted, that is, companies are allowed to submit some materials according to the time limit specified in the notification and commitment letter. &quot;I really feel the convenience of the reform. &quot;
The Shanghai Market Supervision Department stated that it is the first pilot in the country to implement a notification and commitment system for food production licenses.
After the reform, the approval process has been compressed from the previous six links of &quot;registration, acceptance, on-site inspection, sampling inspection, material review, approval and certificate making&quot; to three links of &quot;registration, acceptance, approval and certificate making&quot;, and the processing time has been reduced from before the reform. The 20 working days are shortened to on-site processing.
Taking into account the highly export-oriented characteristics of Pudong&#39;s economy, the Shanghai market supervision department has delegated the registration authority of the permanent representative offices of foreign (regional) enterprises to the Shanghai Free Trade Zone to facilitate enterprises to handle the procedures nearby.
Statistics show that this decentralization involves a total of 1,592 permanent representative offices in the Shanghai Free Trade Zone, 99 of which have been handled in accordance with the new regulations.
