Will MCA contest the Tanjung Piai parliamentary by-election in Johor?
MCA President Datuk Seri Wee Ka Siong: “Leave it to the Supreme Council of the Barisan Nasional for discussion!”
The Tanjung Piai parliamentary seat by-election is about to begin, and whether MCA, a member party of the Barisan Nasional, will contest this traditional parliamentary seat is attracting attention.
However, after the MCA Central Committee held a meeting, it was announced that it would be left to the Supreme Council of the Barisan Nasional to decide whether this traditional MCA seat should continue to be contested by MCA or be replaced by other member parties.
After presiding over the MCA Central Committee meeting on Thursday afternoon, Wei Jiaxiang told the media that any by-election would be conducted by the Barisan Nasional in accordance with the standard operating procedures (SOP), which means that it must be finalized after a meeting of the Barisan Nasional Supreme Council.
He said that since the Election Committee will not meet until next Monday (1st) to finalize the Tanjung Piai parliamentary by-election, the BN Supreme Council meeting is expected to be held in early October.
&quot;Yesterday (26th) morning, I also met with Barisan Nasional Chairman Datuk Seri Ahmad Zahid Hamidi. We all agreed that this seat must be regained from the Pakatan Harapan. &quot;
&quot;We have decided to convene a special BN leadership meeting in early October. The leaders of the three BN parties will determine which member party will join the battle. &quot;
Asked whether MCA would insist on contesting this traditional seat in the Supreme Council of the Barisan Nasional, Wee Ka Siong reiterated that as the president of MCA, he must act in accordance with the standard operating procedures, so any decision must obtain the consensus of the Barisan Nasional.
&quot;In any by-election, it is common for some people to be willing to fight, some political parties and certain parties to think they should come out. &quot;
“The most important thing is what organization and political alliance do we come from?”
&quot;This is a big test for the political alliance we have formed over the years. We believe that the Barisan Front has upheld some valuable values along the way. &quot;
&quot;Someone may say something during this process, and that&#39;s not surprising.&quot;
&quot;However, once the Supreme Council of the Barisan Nasional makes a decision, everyone must prepare for war with all their strength. That is the most valuable thing. &quot;
In any case, Wee Ka Siong said that MCA will make every effort to prepare for the upcoming Tanjong Piai parliamentary by-election at three levels, namely the district committee, the state joint committee and the central government.
“The district committee will be led by (Tanjung Piai) district committee chairman Datuk Seri Wong Jik Sheng; the state joint committee will be led by Datuk Lim Pei Xing, acting chairman of the Johor joint committee; and the central committee will be led by the acting president Dato Ma Hanshun and General Secretary Dato Zhang Shengwen personally deployed. &quot;
Last Saturday (21st), Tanjung Piai MP Datuk Mohd Farid of the Bersatu Party passed away at the Pontian Government Hospital due to heart problems at the age of 42.
A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province was ordered to &quot;compulsorily patrol the mountains&quot; for hunting wild animals.
A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province was sentenced for hunting wild animals and was ordered to compensate 15,420 yuan (RMB, the same below) for the cost of repairing damage to ecological resources and the environment.
Due to the poverty of the defendant&#39;s family, the procuratorial organ used alternative labor to compensate for ecological restoration costs, achieving an organic unity of legal and social effects.
Wang Zhongliang, deputy chief prosecutor of the Baokang County Procuratorate, introduced on the 27th that through three months of &quot;voluntary mountain patrol&quot; and other alternative labor, the defendant Zhou had established a deep relationship with the wild macaques and felt deeply remorseful for his previous behavior of hunting animals. .
On June 21 this year, a civil public interest litigation incidental to a criminal case in the field of ecological resources filed by the Baokang County Procuratorate was heard publicly in the county court and the verdict was pronounced in court.
The defendant Zhou was sentenced to 3 years in prison, suspended for 4 years, and fined 3,000 yuan. He was also ordered to compensate 15,420 yuan for ecological resource and environmental damage repair costs.
After investigation, Zhou began to set up a power grid on the cliff in late January 2014 and hunted more than 20 wild animals, including gorals, muntjacs, and tufted deer.
The goral is a national second-level endangered wild protected animal, and the muntjac and tufted deer are listed in the &quot;National Terrestrial Wildlife Protection List.&quot;
During the trial, Zhou confessed to his illegal facts and actions and was willing to bear additional civil liability.
However, considering the poor economic situation of Zhou&#39;s family, under the coordination of the Baokang County Procuratorate, the local village committee, the forest station, and Zhou reached an agreement on alternative labor compensation for ecological restoration costs: that is, Zhou carried out the work in the village macaque reserve. Macaque domestication, management and protection, voluntary mountain patrols, and forest protection will be provided for one year, and public welfare services will be provided to offset the cost of ecological restoration.
The court recognized the prosecutor&#39;s suggestion and agreed that Zhou should actively fulfill his obligation to &quot;compensate for ecological restoration costs through alternative labor&quot; while executing his suspended sentence.
At present, Zhou has been working voluntarily in the macaque reserve for three months, actively patrolling the mountains and performing well.
In recent years, Baokang County Procuratorate has organically integrated procuratorial functions and social governance behaviors in practice, scientifically used procuratorial suggestions, investigation supervision, litigation supervision and other supervision methods, and used judicial means to minimize the damage caused by criminal acts to the ecological environment.
United Nations awards “Champion of the Earth Award” to “Ant Forest”
Amid warm applause and magnificent music, &quot;Ant Forest&quot; project leader Xu Di and user representative Shen Junliang stepped onto the podium and received the 2019 United Nations &quot;Champions of the Earth Award&quot; trophy from the host.
The 2019 &quot;Champions of the Earth Award&quot; award ceremony was held in New York, USA on the 26th. The &quot;Ant Forest&quot; project, which uses mobile phone applets to drive hundreds of millions of people to participate in environmental protection actions, won the &quot;Inspiration and Action Award&quot;.
A week ago, the United Nations Environment Program announced the winners at its headquarters in Nairobi, the capital of Kenya, but those who attended the award ceremony that day could not hide their excitement.
Inge Andersen, Executive Director of the United Nations Environment Program, said in an interview with Xinhua News Agency that &quot;Ant Forest&quot; is an exciting innovation that allows hundreds of millions of people to take action to understand the environmental challenges faced by mankind and what human beings can do. Do something for the environment.
It uses technology to connect people and the environment, allowing every individual to participate in actions to protect the earth, which will have a huge impact.
&quot;Ant Forest&quot; was launched on the Alipay platform in August 2016 by China&#39;s Ant Financial Services Group (referred to as Ant Financial). Users can record green travel in their daily lives, pay utility bills online and other low-carbon activities in &quot;Ant Forest&quot;. Accumulate &quot;green energy&quot; through actions and &quot;plant trees&quot; on your mobile phone.
Every time a user grows a virtual tree, “Ant Forest” and public welfare partners will plant a real tree in a deserted area.
As of August this year, 500 million &quot;Ant Forest&quot; users have reduced carbon emissions by 7.92 million tons and planted 122 million trees in desertified areas.
In the &quot;Champions of the Earth Award&quot; awarded that day, Costa Rica won the award for its national environmental protection efforts. Carlos Alvarado, the president of Costa Rica who came to receive the award, praised the contribution of &quot;Ant Forest&quot; at the scene, &quot;It can inspire so many people. Participating in green actions is impressive.”
Jing Xiandong, chairman and CEO of Ant Financial, said that the &quot;Champions of the Earth Award&quot; is an affirmation of the &quot;Ant Forest&quot; project.
Technology and open platforms make it possible for everyone to participate in low-carbon life. This honor belongs to all participants.
Jing Xiandong said that &quot;Ant Forest&quot; has affected 500 million people in the past three years, and the goal of &quot;Ant Forest&quot; in the next three years is to drive 1 billion people around the world to participate in low-carbon actions.
While combating desertification and protecting the environment, they are also exploring how to make farmers&#39; income more derived from green mountains and clear waters.
In addition to providing employment opportunities through tree planting, it also hopes to help farmers increase their income through agricultural product development projects, e-commerce platforms, etc.
The public welfare and environmental protection model based on digital technology created by &quot;Ant Forest&quot; has also successfully gone overseas and been used as a reference by other countries.
In June this year, GCash, the largest “e-wallet” in the Philippines, launched the Philippine version of “Ant Forest” to encourage Filipino users to better protect the environment through low-carbon life.
According to reports, GCash will join hands with the Philippine Department of Environment and Natural Resources, environmental public welfare organizations, etc., and plans to plant 365,000 trees in the Philippines within one year of the launch of the project.
The &quot;Champions of the Earth Award&quot; is the United Nations&#39; highest award in the field of environmental protection, awarded annually.
&quot;Ant Forest&quot; won the award. This is the third consecutive year that a green innovation project from China has won the &quot;Incentive and Action Award&quot;, following the construction of Saihanba Forest Farm in China and the &quot;Thousand Village Demonstration and Ten Thousand Village Improvement&quot; project in Zhejiang Province, China. .
Economic and trade frictions affect the &quot;report card&quot; of the U.S. economy.
The U.S. economic &quot;report card&quot; for the second quarter of this year shows that the U.S. gross domestic product (GDP) growth slowed down significantly compared with the previous quarter due to the sharp decline in private sector investment and exports.
Analysts pointed out that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainty they brought were the main reasons for the decline in private sector investment and exports in the second quarter.
The final revised data released by the U.S. Department of Commerce on the 26th showed that U.S. GDP grew at an annual rate of 2% in the second quarter, which was the same as the previously released revised data, but significantly lower than the 3.1% in the first quarter.
Data show that consumption growth became the main factor supporting U.S. economic growth in the second quarter.
Personal consumption expenditures, which account for about 70% of the U.S. economy, increased by 4.6% quarter-on-quarter, driving economic growth by 3.03 percentage points.
In addition, government consumption expenditure and investment drove economic growth by 0.82 percentage points.
However, in the second quarter, private sector investment fell by 6.3% from the previous quarter, dragging down economic growth by 1.16 percentage points in the quarter; exports fell by 5.7% from the previous quarter, and net exports dragged down economic growth by 0.68 percentage points in the quarter.
Barry Knapp, managing partner of the Ironside Macroeconomic Consulting Company in the United States, said that private sector investment not only failed to maintain the growth momentum last year, but also declined sharply. This was because economic and trade frictions and rising uncertainty had a negative impact on business confidence. blow.
Knapp believes that under the influence of policy uncertainty, U.S. corporate capital expenditures are expected to remain in decline next year.
Analysts believe that although consumption growth provided strong support to the U.S. economy in the second quarter, there are increasing signs that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainties they bring have affected consumer confidence and pose a threat to the outlook for U.S. consumption. Negative Effects.
Richard Curtin, the leader of the survey and an economics professor at the University of Michigan, recently said that in a recent survey, 38% of consumers spontaneously mentioned the negative impact of tariffs on the U.S. economy. This proportion was the highest in a year and a half. new high.
Regarding the future trend of the U.S. economy, analysts generally believe that the U.S. economy will continue to slow down.
However, some experts said that if economic and trade frictions are eased, the performance of the U.S. industrial sector and financial markets will improve.
Karen Birch, a global economist at the British Economist Intelligence Unit, predicts that the U.S. economy will continue its gradual downward trend this year and its growth rate will drop to a lower level than in the second quarter.
Mark Zandi, chief economist of Moody&#39;s Analytics, predicts that, assuming that economic and trade frictions do not continue to escalate, the U.S. economic growth will be 2.3% this year and will further slow down to 1.6% next year.
Ellen Hazen, investment manager of Putnam Investment Company, pointed out that the current biggest concern of enterprises is economic and trade disputes and the uncertainty they bring. If the economic and trade disputes can be resolved, the uncertainty will be significantly reduced, and the performance of the industrial sector will be better than Much better now.
Matt Melly, equity strategist at Miller-Tabak Asset Management, said that economic and trade frictions remain the &quot;primary issue&quot; and are also the main cause of the sharp fluctuations in the U.S. capital market this year. Whether the economic and trade frictions can be properly resolved will be a factor that will affect this year. The key to the direction of U.S. capital markets in the remaining time.
Ningxia is the first couple to take joint parental leave, allowing parents of children aged 0 to 3 to take 10 days a year.
Protecting women&#39;s legitimate rights and interests is a reflection of respecting and protecting human rights, and is also an important symbol of social civilization and progress.
On September 27, at the 15th meeting of the Standing Committee of the 12th National People&#39;s Congress of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, the &quot;Regulations on the Protection of Women&#39;s Rights and Interests in the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region&quot; was passed with a high vote.
This is the first local regulation formulated and promulgated at the provincial level in Ningxia to comprehensively and systematically safeguard women&#39;s legitimate rights and interests. It will be officially implemented on November 1, 2019.
It is understood that the &quot;Regulations&quot; passed this time were revised on the basis of the 2007 &quot;Ningxia Measures for the Implementation of the &quot;Law of the People&#39;s Republic of China on the Protection of Women&#39;s Rights and Interests&quot;, and are divided into 9 chapters and 65 articles, including general principles, political rights, culture and education Rights and interests, labor and social security rights, property rights, personal rights, marriage and family rights, legal responsibilities, and by-laws.
In the &quot;Regulations&quot;, Ningxia encourages the exploration and implementation of joint parental leave for couples, which is the first of its kind in the country.
In April this year, the &quot;Guiding Opinions on Promoting the Development of Care Services for Infants and Young Children Under 3 Years Old&quot; promulgated by the General Office of the State Council has relevant descriptions of joint parenting for couples.
In the process of revising the &quot;Regulations&quot;, Ningxia innovatively proposed that &quot;employers are encouraged to provide couples with children who meet the laws and regulations to provide ten days of joint parental leave to each spouse every year when the children are zero to three years old.&quot;
At the same time, the Regulations highlight anti-sexual harassment and the protection of female minors.
Article 43 of the &quot;Regulations&quot; incorporates the latest legislative achievements in the personality rights section of China&#39;s current Civil Code, and stipulates in detail the constituent elements of sexual harassment, the subjects and mechanisms for combating sexual harassment, etc.
Article 44 of the &quot;Regulations&quot; explicitly prohibits frequent sexual assaults on girls and requires educational institutions to carry out relevant education, protection and prevention work, becoming a new benchmark for the protection of girls in local legislation.
Regarding women’s right to know and handle common property in marriage and family, Article 35 of the Regulations clearly stipulates women’s right to know about common property and the obligations of property registration agencies and related entities, providing solid institutional support for women’s rights protection.
In addition, in response to a hot social issue - gender discrimination in employment, Article 26 of the Regulations not only prohibits direct discrimination, but also prohibits indirect discrimination, and absorbs the latest practical experience in joint interviews to strengthen punishment for illegal acts of gender discrimination, Protect women&#39;s legitimate rights and interests more effectively.
In recent years, the Ningxia Women&#39;s Federation has joined forces with the Public Security Bureau, the Civil Affairs Bureau and other departments to promote and introduce professional social forces to participate in the mediation of marriage and family conflicts and anti-domestic violence, and the results have been very remarkable.
The &quot;Regulations&quot; summarize and improve this. Many legal articles encourage the mobilization of social forces and the accumulation of social resources to jointly safeguard women&#39;s rights and interests, and require people&#39;s governments at or above the county level to provide stable and institutional guarantees and support through the purchase of services, etc. .
Inner Mongolia Xing&#39;an League Academician Yuan Longping&#39;s workstation achieves a yield of more than 1,000 kilograms of rice per mu of saline-alkali tolerant rice.
