Finance Minister Liu Kun: 67 central enterprises and financial institutions have transferred 860.1 billion yuan of state-owned assets to replenish social security funds.
Finance Minister Liu Kun said on the 27th that so far, 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions have completed the transfer of part of state-owned capital to enrich social security funds, with a total transfer of state-owned capital of approximately 860.1 billion yuan.
Liu Kun made the above statement at the national task deployment meeting for transferring part of state-owned capital to replenish social security funds jointly held by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, and the State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission on the same day.
&quot;Transferring part of state-owned capital to enrich social security funds is an important measure to reform and improve the basic pension insurance system. It is a full reflection of the universal sharing of the development results of state-owned enterprises and the intergenerational equity of the basic pension insurance system. It is a plan that is based on the present and takes into account the long term. policy measures. &quot;
In 2017, the State Council issued the &quot;Implementation Plan for Transferring Part of State-owned Capital to Enrich Social Security Funds&quot;, requiring the selection of some central enterprises and some provinces to carry out pilot projects.
According to Liu Kun, the preliminary work of the transfer has achieved positive results.
At the central level, three batches of transfers of a total of 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions have been completed, with a total transfer of state-owned capital of approximately 860.1 billion yuan.
Among them, the transfer work of the central financial institution that the Ministry of Finance performs as an investor has been basically completed.
The transfer of central enterprises has reached a certain scale.
At the local level, preliminary work for enterprise transfer has been carried out one after another.
By the end of 2018, the pilot work in Zhejiang and Yunnan provinces had been basically completed, and 15.8 billion yuan and 18.5 billion yuan of state-owned capital had been transferred respectively.
In addition to the pilot provinces, other provinces have also carried out preparatory work for the transfer, laying the foundation for the next implementation of the transfer.
According to a notice jointly issued by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, the State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission, the State Administration of Taxation, and the China Securities Regulatory Commission, the work of transferring part of state-owned capital from the central and local governments to replenish social security funds will be fully launched in 2019 and will be basically completed by the end of 2020.
The meeting held that day made specific arrangements for comprehensively promoting the transfer work.
The meeting emphasized the need to complete the transfer work pragmatically and efficiently.
“According to the schedule, the transfer work will be basically completed by the end of 2020.
The transfer work time is tight and the tasks are heavy. &quot;
Liu Kun said that all regions and departments must carefully organize and arrange carefully to ensure that the transfer work is completed as required; solidly advance the work and accurately grasp the content of the transfer policy; strengthen communication and coordination, and solve difficult problems in a timely manner.
Transfer of state-owned assets to enrich social security funds - Starting from the starting point of &quot;enriching the money bag of social security funds&quot;, the destination is to provide strong support for pension security.
However, the author believes that this is not a simple &quot;physical displacement&quot; of equity, but a &quot;mathematical addition&quot;.
On September 20, the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, the State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission, the State Administration of Taxation, and the China Securities Regulatory Commission jointly issued the &quot;Notice on Comprehensively Promoting the Transfer of Part of State-owned Capital to Enrich Social Security Funds&quot;, clarifying the timetable for the transfer of state-owned assets to social security funds, namely The work of transferring part of state-owned capital from the central and local governments to replenish social security funds was fully launched in 2019.
After the document was released, the Ministry of Finance and other departments implemented it very quickly.
On September 25, the Ministry of Finance transferred all 10% of the equity held by the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China and the Agricultural Bank of China to the Social Security Fund. The total value of the two equity transfers exceeded 115 billion yuan.
According to regulations, social security foundations and other undertaking entities, as financial investors, enjoy the income rights, disposal rights and information rights of the state-owned equity transferred.
ICBC and Agricultural Bank of China stated in the announcement that this change in equity will not lead to changes in the bank’s controlling shareholders and actual controllers.
In this regard, the author believes that similar state-owned enterprise equity transfers are not simple changes in equity ownership, but &quot;addition operations&quot; that can stimulate a series of effects.
The &quot;additive result&quot; of the first step of transferring part of state-owned assets to social security can naturally reflect that state-owned enterprises are owned by all the people and the fruits of development are shared by all.
After years of reform and development, state-owned enterprises, especially central enterprises, are mostly in important industries and fields in my country&#39;s economy, and their overall profitability is strong and stable.
Among them, leading companies continue to become better, bigger and stronger.
On July 10, the State Council executive meeting decided to fully launch the transfer of part of state-owned capital to replenish social security funds this year.
The Ministry of Finance immediately stated that it will work with relevant departments, in accordance with the deployment of the State Council executive meeting, to comprehensively promote the transfer of part of state-owned capital to replenish social security funds, fully reflecting the intergenerational equity of the basic pension insurance system and the universal sharing of the development results of state-owned enterprises.
The second step of the transfer, the &quot;additional result&quot;, is to enhance the sustainability of my country&#39;s social security funds and further consolidate the foundation of the pension social security system.
With the aging of the population, my country&#39;s social security funds are under pressure. Most of the state-owned assets that are transferred this time have the ability to continue to make profits and pay dividends. They can not only effectively supplement the social security funds, but also provide a source of vitality for the social security funds.
Some estimates show that every 3.8 percentage points of state-owned capital transferred can support a 1 percentage point reduction in the corporate basic pension insurance deposit ratio.
The third step of the transfer, the &quot;additional result&quot;, is to add stabilizers to the capital market.
The way for the transferee to obtain income for this transfer is &quot;mainly dividends, supplemented by operations.&quot;
As a financial investor in state-owned capital, social security funds do mainly obtain equity dividend income.
However, as a value investor in the capital market, social security funds have strong capital operation capabilities.
