Jiangxi: “Line Leaders” protect the operational safety of passenger lines.
The reporter learned from the Jiangxi Provincial Highway Transport Administration that as of now, 1,334 passenger lines in Jiangxi’s 11 districts and cities and 6 counties directly under the provincial administration have “line lengths”.
The person in charge of the Jiangxi Provincial Highway Transport Administration said that because the safety management of some passenger transport enterprises is a mere formality, the main safety responsibilities of the enterprises are not fully implemented, and illegal and illegal behaviors such as overcrowding, speeding of passenger vehicles, and driver fatigue driving occur from time to time, and the safety situation of road passenger transport is Rather severe.
In order to further consolidate the main responsibility of road passenger transport enterprises for safety production and ensure the safety of passengers traveling by bus, Jiangxi began to pilot the &quot;line leader system&quot; in 2017 and began to gradually promote it throughout the province in 2018.
At present, 92 road passenger transport companies in Jiangxi have implemented the &quot;line chief system&quot; and selected &quot;line chiefs&quot; to manage 1,334 lines, covering 4,824 operating passenger cars.
According to reports, &quot;line leaders&quot; are generally designated by specialized personnel from road transport and passenger transport enterprises. They are specifically responsible for managing the people, vehicles, lines, etc. of relevant lines, ensuring that the person in charge of the line is responsible for the lines, vehicles, drivers, operating environment, etc. Comprehensive control to ensure the operational safety of the line.
