Fujian Provincial Tax, Treasury and Bank’s convenient comprehensive tax payment platform is officially launched - China News Service
The Fujian Provincial Tax, Treasury and Bank’s convenient comprehensive tax payment platform was officially launched.
China News Service, Fuzhou, September 27 (Ye Qiuyun) The Fujian Provincial Tax and Treasury Bank&#39;s convenient comprehensive tax payment platform was officially launched on September 27 in Fuzhou City, Fujian Province.
The reporter learned that on October 26, 2018, the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People&#39;s Bank of China, the Fujian Provincial Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation, and China UnionPay Co., Ltd. jointly signed a tripartite cooperation memorandum to create the first comprehensive tax service in Fujian Province for the convenience of the public. Payment platform.
After nearly a year of construction, the platform has been successfully launched.
Wang Dehui, director of the Treasury Department of the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People&#39;s Bank of China, introduced that the platform adheres to the construction concepts of security, versatility, convenience, compliance and leadership, and the front end connects taxation, government, banks, non-bank payment institutions and society. The service provider provides multiple online and offline tax payment channels such as mobile APP, WeChat public account, tax hall, bank branches, inclusive financial service points, etc., and connects the national treasury and tax system at the back end.
It is reported that the platform brings together a number of projects that benefit the people and facilitate the people, among which the project for checking and paying medical insurance premiums for urban and rural residents has been officially launched.
The project has opened up 14 online and offline channels and can provide services to more than 30 million urban and rural residents in Fujian Province, covering 76% of the permanent population of Fujian Province.
Medical premiums can be paid online through &quot;Min Tax Tong&quot;, &quot;Cloud QuickPass&quot;, various banks&#39; APPs, WeChat public accounts, etc.; offline, you can scan the QR code at various tax halls and rural inclusive financial service points in Fujian Province. Pay medical premiums through various methods such as , swiping or swiping your card.
Shi Dong, deputy president of the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People&#39;s Bank of China, said that the successful launch of the platform can provide the public with safe, efficient, multi-channel and multi-mode convenient payment while ensuring direct payment of government revenue into the treasury and real-time interaction of data and information. Tax services.
At present, more than 9,000 of the province&#39;s more than 16,000 inclusive financial service points have opened the function of checking and paying medical premiums, allowing rural residents to check and pay their medical premiums without leaving the village, giving the public more and more options. The stronger the &quot;sense of gain&quot; and &quot;happiness&quot;.
According to statistics, since the 20-day trial run of the platform&#39;s urban and rural residents&#39; medical premium checking and payment project, the number of service users has reached 840,000, including 750,000 online payment users and nearly 20,000 inclusive financial service point payment users.
In addition, Lin Guojing, deputy director of the Fujian Provincial Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation, revealed at the event that the platform is the first in the country to apply blockchain electronic payment voucher technology.
Starting next month, payers can download stamped electronic payment vouchers directly through their mobile phones after completing payment.
The Fujian tax information network based on blockchain technology is being built, and the &quot;highway&quot; to facilitate tax payment for the people will be further broadened.
