Two major ultra-high voltage projects, &quot;One, One, One, All&quot;, were put into operation
On the 26th, the Zhundong to Wannan ±1100 kV UHV DC transmission project and the Sutong 1000 kV AC UHV GIL integrated pipeline project were put into operation.
Both projects occupy the commanding heights in their respective fields of current world power transmission technology. Once put into operation, they will greatly improve the large-scale optimal allocation of energy in our country.
Guo Zhi, chief economist of the National Energy Administration, said that the Zhundong to Wannan project is the transmission project with the largest power transmission capacity and the longest transmission distance in the world.
Its operation is of great significance to promoting the development of Xinjiang energy base and ensuring the power supply in East China.
GIL stands for gas insulated metal enclosed transmission line.
The Sutong Pipeline Gallery Project has set a record for the GIL project with the highest voltage level and strongest transmission capacity in the world, and has achieved the closed-loop operation of the &#39;AC double-ring network&#39; with the highest voltage level in East China&#39;s backbone power grid.
According to the State Grid Corporation of China, the power transmission distance of the Zhundong to Wannan project is 3,324 kilometers.
If conventional technology is used, more than 15% of the electric energy will be lost in transit. However, through research and development of this project, the economic transmission distance has been greatly increased to more than 3,000 kilometers.
After the Zhundong to Wannan project is put into operation, it will be able to transmit 100 million kWh of electricity every 8 hours and 20 minutes, which can help solve the problem of existing new energy consumption in Xinjiang.
Based on full load estimates, the annual power transmission of this line alone will reach 60 to 85 billion kilowatt hours, which can meet more than half of Shanghai&#39;s annual electricity consumption.
The Sutong GIL integrated pipe gallery project is a control project for the UHV AC ring network across the Yangtze River.
If conventional overhead lines are used to cross the river, two giant towers over 450 meters tall will need to be built on the Yangtze River, and an artificial island larger than four football fields will need to be built for each tower.
In this regard, State Grid boldly innovated and developed compact UHV AC GIL transmission technology to cross the river underwater through tunnels to avoid impact on the golden waterway.
The two projects have promoted my country&#39;s electrical equipment manufacturing capabilities to achieve a new leap.
At present, the State Grid has completed a total of &quot;10 AC and 11 DC&quot; UHV projects, and there are still &quot;4 AC and 3 DC&quot; projects under construction.
