The reporter learned from the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences on the 27th that Spodoptera Frugiperda has been effectively controlled in Yunnan, without causing large-scale outbreaks and disasters. The prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In January this year, Spodoptera Frugiperda that had migrated from abroad was discovered for the first time in Jiangcheng County, Pu&#39;er City, Yunnan Province, and was subsequently confirmed to occur in 129 counties in Yunnan. Spodoptera Fugiperda also gradually spread from Yunnan to mainland China, posing a direct impact on China&#39;s grain production. threaten.
Spodoptera Frugiperda is an important polyphagous long-distance migratory agricultural pest native to tropical and subtropical regions of the Americas. It is a major migratory pest in the global warning of the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization. It has &quot;international, migratory, and outbreak characteristics.&quot; &quot;sexual, destructive&quot; characteristics.
This pest harms more than 80 crops such as corn, sugarcane, and sorghum. It feeds heavily and can cause yield losses of up to 70%.
Control is difficult, and there are currently no registered pesticides to control this insect in China.
Since Spodoptera Frugiperda migrated and invaded Yunnan, the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences selected researcher Chen Aidong to lead the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences&#39; agricultural cross-border pest collaborative green prevention and control provincial innovation team to go to the front line to conduct field surveys, collect samples, and carry out Technical guidance and test demonstration.
Chen Aidong&#39;s team has initially grasped the population characteristics of Yunnan Spodoptera Frugiperda, natural enemy insect resources, characteristics of overseas insect sources, population migration trajectories, pesticide toxicity and field control effects.
They actively carry out research and application of green prevention and control technologies. Through the implementation of new green prevention and control technologies such as population monitoring, adult insect trapping, scientific use of pesticides and agronomic measures, the prevention and control effect in the demonstration area has reached more than 90%, while reducing chemical The use of pesticides protects natural enemy resources and the ecological environment, and provides technical support for effective control of Spodoptera Frugiperda outbreaks and sustainable management in Yunnan.
At present, Spodoptera Frugiperda has been effectively controlled in Yunnan, without causing large-scale outbreaks and disasters. The prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In the next step, the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences will focus on the ecological mechanism of population migration and invasion outbreaks, and break through the construction of biological prevention and green prevention and control technology systems.
At the same time, we actively promote cross-border international cooperation and strive to establish joint key laboratories, joint monitoring sites and demonstration areas overseas to enhance Yunnan’s all-round monitoring and early warning capabilities for Spodoptera Frugiperda.
