Tianjin Chow Tai Fook, the tallest building in northern China, was completed and created more than 100 national patents
The completion ceremony of Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Financial Center, the tallest building in northern China, was held on the afternoon of the 26th in Tianjin Binhai New Area. It marked the building information model independently developed by the Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Financial Center Project Department of China Construction Eighth Engineering Group Co., Ltd. and won the Global Excellence Award in the Global Engineering Construction Industry. The collaborative management platform of accurate BIM models has been successful in the field of skyscraper construction.
Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Financial Center is located in Tianjin Economic and Technological Development Zone. The total construction area of the project is 390,000 square meters, with 4 underground floors, 100 floors above ground, and a building height of 530 meters. It covers Grade A offices, luxury apartments, super five-star hotels, etc. , after completion, it will become an important part of Tianjin’s international landmark building complex.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Financial Center Project Department of China Construction Eighth Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the entire project uses more than 70,000 tons of steel, and the high-altitude butt welds are about 376,000 meters, equivalent to the height of 42.5 Mount Everest, and the welding wire can circle the earth. 40 laps, the number of steel components reaches 42,000, and more than 50% are non-standard components, including the world&#39;s largest double-tube elliptical cross-section steel tube column with a twist angle of 90 degrees.
The complexity and processing difficulty of the steel structure of the Tianjin Chow Tai Fook project are unprecedented.
According to industry insiders, Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Financial Center is the first to fully implement Building Information Modeling (BIM) management among skyscraper projects that have been completed or are under construction across the country.
Creatively proposed and successfully implemented the &quot;Three Complete BIM Application&quot; model of full participation, full professional application, and full process implementation, and developed a collaborative management platform based on high-precision BIM models.
The person in charge said that during the construction process of Chow Tai Fook, the project department first carried out BIM construction in the virtual world, and then carried out scientific and accurate verification before proceeding with physical construction, thereby eliminating the problems of dismantling, modification and rework that may have occurred in the construction of previous construction projects. nipped in the bud.
In 2017, the BIM innovation achievements of the Chow Tai Fook Financial Center project won the first prize in the construction group of the Global Engineering Construction Industry Global Excellence Award at the Global AU Masters Forum and the 2017 Global Engineering Construction Industry Global Excellence Awards Ceremony.
During the construction process of the project, the project department created more than 130 national patents.
It is worth mentioning that the BIM innovation results and technological innovation promotion of the Tianjin Chow Tai Fook project not only enabled all complex and numerous construction links to be optimized at once, shortening the construction period by more than four months, but also led to significant improvements in safety management and other aspects. .
Not long ago, the Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Financial Center project also won the 2019 ISA International Security Award.
The 86th China-Laos, Myanmar-Thailand joint patrol and law enforcement on the Mekong River was completed.
Reporters learned from the Information Office of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Department on the 27th that at 15:30 that day, three Chinese law enforcement boats and two Lao law enforcement boats participating in the 86th joint patrol and law enforcement of the Mekong River between China, Laos, Myanmar, and Thailand successfully docked at Guanlei Port in China. This marks the successful conclusion of this joint patrol law enforcement operation.
The operation was launched in Guanlei Port on the 24th and lasted 4 days and 3 nights. A total of 136 law enforcement personnel and 6 law enforcement boats were dispatched from China, Laos, Myanmar and Thailand.
During the operation, the formation carried out joint patrols, anti-drug publicity and other activities in key waters such as the Golden Triangle, Ban Xianggoo and Muang Mo in Laos.
In addition, China also sent a group of practical police instructors to the 122nd and 133rd Border Defense Companies of the Lao People&#39;s Army to conduct practical police skills exchanges, effectively improving the emergency response capabilities of law enforcement teams from both sides to jointly handle emergencies.
The four countries of China, Laos, Myanmar, and Thailand also held a law enforcement cooperation exchange meeting in Chiang Saen, Thailand. They informed each other of the recent border management, combating drug crimes, and the security situation in the Mekong River Basin. They also discussed and exchanged information on strengthening information exchange, research and judgment, and law enforcement cooperation, and reached an agreement. Consensus; and organized cultural and sports exchange activities among the four countries, and carried out competitions such as football, sepak takraw, iron ball and tug-of-war to effectively enhance mutual understanding among law enforcement team members and law enforcement cooperation and friendship among the four countries.
