Chengdu “Panda Planet” and Giant Panda Breeding Research Base Expansion Project Starts
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, September 27 (Reporter Li Qianwei) Enriching giant panda cultural themed tourism routes, the panda base can accommodate 180 giant pandas in the future. The &quot;Panda Planet&quot; and Giant Panda Breeding Research Base expansion project officially started in Chengdu on the 25th, which means that the &quot;Panda Capital&quot; project planned by Chengdu was officially launched.
According to the plan, the &quot;Panda City&quot; to be built in Chengdu consists of three areas: Beihu Area, Dujiangyan Area and Longquan Mountain Area, covering an area of 69 square kilometers.
The plan organically combines the ecological and cultural value of giant pandas with the construction of a beautiful and livable park city in Chengdu to create an ecological home for giant pandas.
&quot;Panda Planet&quot; belongs to the Beihu area, covering an area of 35 square kilometers. Combined with industrial planning, it will form a &quot;1+N+X&quot; regional spatial structure.
1 core attraction is the reconstruction and expansion project of the Giant Panda Breeding Research Base; N cultural tourism consumption scenes are created, namely Panda Town, Xiaoyao Garden, Dream Garden, etc.; X regional basic supporting facilities.
After the reconstruction and expansion of the Chengdu Giant Panda Breeding Research Base, the scale will reach 3,525 acres. It is overall positioned as a world-class giant panda protection demonstration site and a place where people and animals can share quality time.
The park is planned to accommodate 180 giant pandas and their companion animals (red pandas and golden monkeys).
